Package org.jsapar.parse

For reading input and building the canonical data model described in the org.jsapar.model package.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LineEventListener
    Interface for receiving event call-backs while parsing.
    ParseTask
    Common interface for all parse jobs.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractParser
    Abstract base class for all parsers.
    AbstractParseTask
    Abstract implementation of ParseTask interface.
    CellParser
    Internal class for parsing text on cell level.
    DocumentBuilderLineEventListener
    This line event listener can be used to build a document based on line events.
    LineDecoratorErrorEventListener
    Internal class.
    LineParsedEvent
    Event object that is sent as event to all LineEventListener instances of a parser for each line while parsing.
    MulticastLineEventListener
    Distributes all line events to multiple LineEventListener instances.
    ValidationHandler
    Internal utility class for handling validation error.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CellParseException
    This class is used as a way for the parser to report back parsing errors.
    LineParseException
    Exception that occurs while parsing and that affects the line and not a single cell.

Package org.jsapar.parse Description

For reading input and building the canonical data model described in the org.jsapar.model package. The input can be a text source such as a file or it can be a Java Bean structure. If you have any other type of input such as a database table cursor, you can build your own parser by implementing the ParseTask interface.
